 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality COVID-19 Disaster Management Forum advised residents that the issuing of all permits that were done through the municipality or the forum has been put on hold. "This is following the address by President Ramaphosa on Thursday where he indicated that some of the lockdown regulations will be adjusted," the municipality said. "The forum and the municipality wants to afford itself an opportunity to empower themselves with the new adjusted regulations that will be published through different relevant government departments over the weekend and next week. "Updates on this matter will be made during the course of the week." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 